# .gitignore — system-design-bot
# A markdown/skill content repo. Keep it focused: ignore OS junk, editor temp,
# secrets, and the coach's scratch area. (No node/python build artifacts here.)

# ── OS / filesystem cruft ───────────────────────────────────────────
.DS_Store
Thumbs.db
Desktop.ini
$RECYCLE.BIN/

# ── Editor / IDE temp files ─────────────────────────────────────────
*.swp
*.swo
*~
.idea/
# NOTE: .vscode/ is intentionally NOT ignored — you may want to commit
# shared settings (e.g. recommended extensions). The skill deliverables
# live in .github/skills/ and .claude/skills/ and MUST stay tracked.

# ── Secrets / local env (defensive; none used yet) ──────────────────
.env
.env.*
*.local

# ── Coach: scratch drafts (inbox is a staging area) ─────────────────
# Keep the README; ignore loose drafts that haven't been filed yet.
coach/inbox/*
!coach/inbox/README.md

# ── Coach: local/generated practice problems ────────────────────────
# Keep the curated seed bank tracked; store generated or personal
# problem drafts here until you intentionally promote them.
coach/problems/local/

# ── Coach: personal practice sessions ───────────────────────────────
# Your sessions (transcripts, answers, scorecards) are TRACKED by default
# so your progress history is versioned and backed up.
# If you plan to SHARE / publish this repo, uncomment the two lines below
# to keep your personal practice data out of git:
coach/sessions/*
!coach/sessions/README.md
